eals to scholars, students, advocates and others concerned about addressing some of the most profound and enduring injustices of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aReparations for historical injusticesvCase studies. 0aReparations for historical injustices. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  aColombian.  aColonization.  aIndigenous Guatemalan women.  aMau Mau.  aNakba.  aPalestinian refugees.  aReparations.  aRomani genocide.  aSlavery.  aStarvation crimes.  astructural racism.1 aBassett, Mary T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeckles, Sir Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhabha, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhabha, Jacqueline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConley, Bridget, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElkins, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElkins, Caroline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFischbach, Michael R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFord, Aileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrance, Mireille Fanon Mendes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrivet, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHancock, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImmler, Nicole L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Douglas A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhalidi, Rashid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatache, Margareta, econ